725391f-d.text:
50th Street, (in line thereof) north of Twenty-fifth Avenue (probably in St. Michaels Cemetery), showing four views of the D. Riker farmhouse. It was erected by Abraham Riker about 1717. Additions have since it was first erected been made. The British plundered this house when it was occupied by Jacobus Riker in 1776. See other views for more
data.
April 1923
Views 1,2 3 and 4
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
